Earlier today I had a “client” reach out and said they had an appointment with me next week, so I go to look for her booking in my agenda and there wasn’t any matching information with her booking.⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣Apparently she booked me under an agency, ⁣
⁣Let me be 100% clear, I am not with any agency in Las Vegas, if you see some of “MY” work under any agency, they’re completely lying to you. I AM NOT UNDER CONTRACT WITH ANYONE IN VEGAS. ⁣
⁣⁣
⁣With that said, I am very grateful for everyone who has booked. I am honored, and I can’t wait to meet y’all. ⁣
⁣I just sold my last available Saturday in September. 🥹⁣

Ava - Clean dewy skin, nude pink lips with a soft brown liner, half lashes and body bronzer. ⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣One thing I been hearing all over the city from clients is how unhappy they were with their previous mua, let me tell y’all something. Over the years I’ve learned that most clients don’t know how to ask for what they want. And when you ask for pictures, most clients will show you 5 different imagines all with different styles, and different skin finishes. My advice to most mua’s “ask questions”⁣
⁣⁣
⁣To all of you who have been booking for this upcoming year, thank you all so much. I appreciate it.
